description: Numbers n with at least as many non-unitary divisors (A048105) as unitary divisors (A034444).
comments: Numbers divisible by a prime cubed or two distinct primes squared. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Jun 07 2013
maple: with(numtheory): for n from 1 to 800 do if 2^nops(ifactors(n)[2])<=tau(n)-2^nops(ifactors(n)[2]) then printf(`%d,`,n) fi; od:
